{
  "abstract": "The problem\r\nMillions of smallholder  farmers in the rainfed\r\nsemi-arid tropics of theIndian subcontinentdepend on groundnut,  sunflower, cotton and   vegetable crops for their livelihood. A new threat to\r\ngroundnut emerged in\r\n2000 in the form of a   virus that causes lethal necrosis. The virus cameto light in the district of Anantapur, a majorgroundnut producing area in India. This diseasepeanut stem necrosis disease (PSND), destroyed\r\n the majority of the crop in the dsitrict",
